<item>
            <title>[JCR-1819] JCR2SPI: Add specific deep loading of Nodes and Properties</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1819</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>with jcr2spi an item is &amp;#39;deep&amp;#39; loaded whenever the hierarchy is not complete. while for Session#itemExists or Session#getItem it is ok to try loading a Node first and if not found a Property, this is inconvenient (and generates unnecessary round trips to the SPI) for those cases, where the original JCR call indicates whether a Node or Property is expected.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This is the case for Node.getNode(String relPath) and Node.getProperty(String relPath) ((and maybe others))&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Therefore i suggest to add specific methods&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
HierarchyManager#getNodeEntry&lt;br/&gt;
HierarchyManager#getPropertyEntry&lt;br/&gt;
NodeEntry#getDeepNodeEntry&lt;br/&gt;
NodeEntry#getDeepPropertyEntry&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
(or something similar)</description>
